00:13:26,329 --> 00:13:28,079
Frank Jr. Jr.?

271
00:13:28,389 --> 00:13:31,310
You'd be getting a really good one.

272
00:13:31,310 --> 00:13:33,660
He's really funny.

273
00:13:33,660 --> 00:13:37,520
Like, the other day, he made up this joke:

274
00:13:37,889 --> 00:13:39,309
What's green and says,

275
00:13:39,309 --> 00:13:41,100
"Hey, I'm a frog"?

276
00:13:42,270 --> 00:13:44,260
A talking frog.

277
00:13:46,799 --> 00:13:50,050
Oh, no, you can't have him, he's too funny.

278
00:13:50,689 --> 00:13:53,369
Well, all right, that's fine. What about Leslie?

279
00:13:53,419 --> 00:13:56,220
Oh, no, no, not Leslie. No.

280
00:13:56,270 --> 00:13:57,569
She's the only one that knows

281
00:13:57,569 --> 00:13:59,439
how to burp the alphabet.

282
00:14:01,129 --> 00:14:02,489
All right, so that leaves Chandler.

283
00:14:02,489 --> 00:14:03,920
No, no, you can't have Chandler.

284
00:14:03,970 --> 00:14:06,399
No, no. She's my little genius.

285
00:14:06,449 --> 00:14:07,980
I got big hopes for her.

286
00:14:08,030 --> 00:14:11,639
She's gonna be a doctor or a realtor.

287
00:14:14,190 --> 00:14:17,799
Wow, Frank, I think we just ran out of kids.

288
00:14:19,319 --> 00:14:21,270
Oh, I think you're right.

289
00:14:24,150 --> 00:14:25,409
Oh, wow. Phoebe,

290
00:14:25,409 --> 00:14:28,869
I don't think I can give one of them up.

291
00:14:29,220 --> 00:14:31,289
I mean, you know, they drive me crazy,

292
00:14:31,289 --> 00:14:32,559
but they're my babies.

293
00:14:35,580 --> 00:14:37,180
I'm sorry, Frank,

294
00:14:37,180 --> 00:14:38,630
I didn't realize things were so bad.

295
00:14:38,990 --> 00:14:40,540
You know, I'll help out more.

296
00:14:40,540 --> 00:14:42,529
I can baby-sit anytime you want.

297
00:14:42,580 --> 00:14:43,939
You name the day and I'll be there.

298
00:14:43,989 --> 00:14:45,180
How about tomorrow?

299
00:14:45,189 --> 00:14:46,079
Well, that's not good.

300
00:14:47,559 --> 00:14:50,759
But I can move some stuff around and I'll be there.

301
00:14:50,809 --> 00:14:53,039
You and Alice just take the whole day together.

302
00:14:53,609 --> 00:14:55,420
You'd do that for us?

303
00:14:55,470 --> 00:14:56,399
Are you kidding?

304
00:14:56,399 --> 00:14:57,730
That's what sisters are for.

305
00:15:03,540 --> 00:15:05,500
Oh, look at them.

306
00:15:07,140 --> 00:15:09,809
I love you so much.

307
00:15:10,550 --> 00:15:12,759
Oh, crap, don't wake up...

308
00:15:16,740 --> 00:15:18,230
Where are Bill and Colleen?

309
00:15:18,230 --> 00:15:19,889
They are in the kitchen, getting something to eat.

310
00:15:20,109 --> 00:15:21,569
Can you believe how nice they are?

311
00:15:21,619 --> 00:15:22,860
We have to leave.

312
00:15:24,499 --> 00:15:27,139
Why? What did you do in the bathroom?

313
00:15:27,739 --> 00:15:29,260
I didn't get to the bathroom.

314
00:15:29,270 --> 00:15:30,479
I bumped into Owen on the way.

315
00:15:30,529 --> 00:15:32,489
He didn't know he was adopted.

316
00:15:32,500 --> 00:15:33,329
There's a slight chance...

317
00:15:33,379 --> 00:15:34,869
...l may have told him.

318
00:15:35,380 --> 00:15:37,020
Oh, my God, where's my purse?

319
00:15:37,020 --> 00:15:38,799
No, I can replace everything in there.

320
00:15:38,849 --> 00:15:40,520
- Get that binder and let's go!  - Hi.

321
00:15:41,999 --> 00:15:44,199
Some little snacks for everybody.

322
00:15:44,249 --> 00:15:47,299
You don't have to eat the sour worms. Those are for Owen.

323
00:15:47,969 --> 00:15:49,289
I'll go get him in a second.

324
00:15:49,339 --> 00:15:50,750
By the way, you should know,

325
00:15:50,799 --> 00:15:52,790
we haven't told him he's adopted yet.

326
00:15:53,650 --> 00:15:55,330
But kids are so intuitive.

327
00:15:55,860 --> 00:15:58,149
Don't you think, on some level, he already knows?

328
00:15:58,199 --> 00:16:01,339
- I'm adopted?  - See? Intuitive.

329
00:16:02,070 --> 00:16:04,110
What? Where did you hear that?

330
00:16:04,300 --> 00:16:05,559
He told me.

331
00:16:07,199 --> 00:16:10,380
And he paid me 50 dollars not to tell.

332
00:16:11,329 --> 00:16:13,810
Which, technically, now you should give back.

333
00:16:16,799 --> 00:16:18,900
You told him he's adopted?

334
00:16:18,950 --> 00:16:19,799
I'm sorry.

335
00:16:19,799 --> 00:16:21,889
But You should have a sign out there or something.

336
00:16:21,889 --> 00:16:25,409
Or at least whisper it to people when they come in the door.

337
00:16:25,409 --> 00:16:26,890
"Owen doesn't know he's adopted,

338
00:16:26,890 --> 00:16:28,969
and he also thinks Santa is real."

339
00:16:28,969 --> 00:16:31,029
He isn't?

340
00:16:32,150 --> 00:16:34,529
We have to get out of here, baby.

341
00:16:37,450 --> 00:16:41,140
Everyone, I would like to make a toast...

342
00:16:41,190 --> 00:16:44,209
...to Rachel and Joey.

343
00:16:46,129 --> 00:16:49,219
And to love.

344
00:16:51,830 --> 00:16:53,510
Ah, love!

345
00:16:55,300 --> 00:16:57,569
L-O-V-E. Love.

346
00:16:58,110 --> 00:17:00,159
L is for "life."

347
00:17:00,209 --> 00:17:02,630
And what is life without love?

348
00:17:04,140 --> 00:17:05,929
Oh, my God, are we supposed to answer?

349
00:17:07,749 --> 00:17:11,009
O is for...

350
00:17:12,379 --> 00:17:13,760
"Oh, wow!"

351
00:17:17,059 --> 00:17:20,870
The V is for this...

352
00:17:20,919 --> 00:17:24,479
...very surprising turn of events...

353
00:17:25,339 --> 00:17:28,839
...which I am still fine with, by the way.

354
00:17:30,569 --> 00:17:31,729
E...

355
00:17:35,550 --> 00:17:37,169
...is for how...

356
00:17:37,609 --> 00:17:40,869
...extremely normal I find it...

357
00:17:41,360 --> 00:17:43,119
...that you two...

358
00:17:44,899 --> 00:17:46,319
...are together.

359
00:17:48,399 --> 00:17:51,569
And that one day you might get married...

360
00:17:54,180 --> 00:17:56,779
...and have children of your own.

361
00:18:01,269 --> 00:18:04,149
- Dude, are you okay? - Totally.

362
00:18:06,169 --> 00:18:07,780
Ross, you don't seem okay.

363
00:18:07,830 --> 00:18:08,740
I'm sorry,

364
00:18:08,740 --> 00:18:11,100
it must be the pressure of entertaining.

365
00:18:14,969 --> 00:18:18,169
I think everyone would feel better if we had some flan.

366
00:18:18,920 --> 00:18:22,559
Wait, Ross. Ross, l--I have to take off.

367
00:18:22,609 --> 00:18:24,409
- No!  - I'm sorry.

368
00:18:24,460 --> 00:18:26,650
I have an early class in the morning.

369
00:18:27,159 --> 00:18:30,429
But this has been lovely.

370
00:18:31,719 --> 00:18:35,779
Wasn't it? And you thought it would be awkward with Joey.

371
00:18:35,829 --> 00:18:38,290
And that you never really liked Rachel.

372
00:18:39,340 --> 00:18:40,830
You are on fire!

373
00:18:40,830 --> 00:18:43,810
I'll call you in the morning, okay?

374
00:18:43,860 --> 00:18:45,200
- Okay. - All right.

375
00:18:48,710 --> 00:18:50,750
God, Rachel, what Ross just said, that's just--

376
00:18:50,799 --> 00:18:53,000
That's okay. Girls tend not to like me.

377
00:18:54,130 --> 00:18:55,520
Fine.

378
00:18:58,009 --> 00:19:01,880
Okay. I guess it's just flan for three.

379
00:19:03,979 --> 00:19:05,329
Hey, that rhymes.

380
00:19:08,129 --> 00:19:11,500
You know what, Ross, I think we're gonna take off too.

381
00:19:12,639 --> 00:19:16,319
Of course. God, I'm so stupid.

382
00:19:16,369 --> 00:19:18,080
You guys are a couple now.

383
00:19:18,080 --> 00:19:20,430
I mean, you probably just want to be alone.

384
00:19:20,430 --> 00:19:22,289
No, it's just getting late--

385
00:19:22,289 --> 00:19:24,560
It's fine. It's totally fine.

386
00:19:24,560 --> 00:19:27,700
I've got plenty of margaritas. It's all good.

387
00:19:33,999 --> 00:19:36,019
I don't even know what that's for.

388
00:19:42,010 --> 00:19:43,930
You know what?

389
00:19:43,930 --> 00:19:46,989
I think I'm gonna stay here and make sure he's okay.

390
00:19:47,039 --> 00:19:49,060
That's probably a good idea.

391
00:19:49,070 --> 00:19:50,170
I'll see you in the morning.

392
00:19:50,779 --> 00:19:51,660
Okay.

393
00:19:52,880 --> 00:19:54,470
Yeah, you know, Joey, l--

394
00:19:54,619 --> 00:19:56,209
I don't think he's ever gonna

395
00:19:56,209 --> 00:19:57,689
be okay with this.

396
00:19:57,689 --> 00:19:59,870
It doesn't look good, does it?

397
00:20:20,419 --> 00:20:21,619
Morning.

398
00:20:21,859 --> 00:20:24,309
- Here you go.  - Thanks.

399
00:20:25,040 --> 00:20:28,590
- Did you stay here all night?  - Yeah.

400
00:20:30,200 --> 00:20:33,189
So you took off my pants and shoes?

401
00:20:34,060 --> 00:20:35,349
No...

402
00:20:35,399 --> 00:20:36,850
You actually did that when you  were

403
00:20:36,900 --> 00:20:39,390
dancing to the <i>Chicago</i> soundtrack.

404
00:20:41,949 --> 00:20:44,539
Look, Ross...

405
00:20:45,119 --> 00:20:46,819
...about Rachel and l.

406
00:20:46,830 --> 00:20:48,529
Listen, you don't have to worry about that...

407
00:20:48,580 --> 00:20:50,480
...because nothing's gonna happen.

408
00:20:51,089 --> 00:20:52,380
What do you mean?

409
00:20:54,060 --> 00:20:55,559
She and I said from the beginning...

410
00:20:55,559 --> 00:20:56,940
...we weren't gonna do anything

411
00:20:56,940 --> 00:20:58,489
unless you were okay with it.

412
00:20:58,660 --> 00:21:00,150
And clearly--

413
00:21:00,590 --> 00:21:02,980
What are you talking about? I'm fine.

414
00:21:03,750 --> 00:21:07,570
It's okay, Ross. You know, I totally understand.

415
00:21:07,620 --> 00:21:10,160
Of course you're not fine. You're...

416
00:21:11,990 --> 00:21:13,969
You're Ross and Rachel.

417
00:21:15,830 --> 00:21:17,530
Yeah, except we're not.

418
00:21:18,900 --> 00:21:21,889
I mean, we haven't been a couple in, like...

419
00:21:24,350 --> 00:21:26,270
...six years.

420
00:21:28,140 --> 00:21:30,549
My God, is that right?

421
00:21:31,860 --> 00:21:33,220
Has it been that long?

422
00:21:33,990 --> 00:21:35,639
That's what I hear, yeah.

423
00:21:37,690 --> 00:21:41,109
This is crazy.I mean, six years...

424
00:21:41,159 --> 00:21:44,740
...and because of me, you guys aren't gonna be together?

425
00:21:46,359 --> 00:21:47,809
Can I ask you something?

426
00:21:48,689 --> 00:21:49,860
Really...

427
00:21:50,940 --> 00:21:53,659
...what is this thing with you and Rachel?

428
00:21:55,649 --> 00:21:58,799
Come on, you know me. You know...

429
00:22:00,879 --> 00:22:01,729
Joey.

430
00:22:08,399 --> 00:22:10,099
I'm crazy about her.

431
00:22:15,730 --> 00:22:17,890
And she feels the same way?

432
00:22:20,460 --> 00:22:21,979
I think so.

433
00:22:25,049 --> 00:22:26,310
Well, then...

434
00:22:26,700 --> 00:22:29,059
...maybe it's time we all moved on.

435
00:22:29,790 --> 00:22:32,220
Yeah, but, Ross, I mean, you're not okay with it, so--

436
00:22:32,360 --> 00:22:35,729
No, but I want to be.

437
00:22:37,579 --> 00:22:38,969
I will be.

438
00:22:42,250 --> 00:22:44,840
Besides, I'm with Charlie, right?

439
00:22:45,250 --> 00:22:47,740
Oh, my God, I'm still with Charlie, aren't l?

440
00:22:47,790 --> 00:22:49,880
- She didn't see the dance, did she?  - No...

441
00:22:51,710 --> 00:22:54,669
No, that was--That was just for me.

442
00:22:58,980 --> 00:23:00,599
Hey, you...?

443
00:23:01,129 --> 00:23:02,700
You sure about this?

444
00:23:03,270 --> 00:23:05,159
Yeah, I'm sure.

445
00:23:08,190 --> 00:23:08,999
And...

446
00:23:10,400 --> 00:23:12,139
...we're okay?

447
00:23:24,329 --> 00:23:25,989
- Hey, Pheebs. - Hey.

448
00:23:25,989 --> 00:23:27,789
We just want to give you a heads up.

449
00:23:27,959 --> 00:23:29,849
- Bill and Colleen hate us.  - Why?

450
00:23:29,849 --> 00:23:31,300
Owen didn't know he's adopted

451
00:23:31,300 --> 00:23:32,489
and Monica told him.

452
00:23:32,489 --> 00:23:33,359
What?

453
00:23:33,909 --> 00:23:36,130
Still, he had to find out sometime.

454
00:23:36,180 --> 00:23:37,110
How would you like it

455
00:23:37,110 --> 00:23:38,220
if someone told the triplets

456
00:23:38,270 --> 00:23:39,950
that you gave birth to them?

457
00:23:44,990 --> 00:23:46,049
I'm gonna go tell Emma

458
00:23:46,049 --> 00:23:47,109
she was an accident.

